{{Quote|Chrom-Vrone [sic], legacy of the Yuuzhan Vong occupation, still pock the planet Wayland. Scars of war.|[[Wolf Sazen]]|<ref name="Legacy (2006) 43">[[Legacy (2006) 43|''Legacy'' (2006) 43]]</ref>}}
'''Chom-Vrone''' were large worms used as drills by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]. They were shaped like cylinders, a hundred meters high and nearly that many wide, made of [[yorik coral]]. Chom-Vrone digested rock, turning it into a semi-[[Plasma/Legends|plasmatic]] state in a process that was similar to that carried out by [[Yaret-Kor]] cannons on [[Yorik-et|coralskippers]]. When a Chom-Vrone had a full load, hundreds of meter-wide tubes would extend from the top of the Chom-Vrone, spewing the plasma out onto the surrounding ground. This had the added effect of keeping the perimeter clear and any undesirables out of the region.

After the [[Yuuzhan Vong War|war]] ended, many Chom-Vrone remained on the [[Terraforming/Legends|ravaged]] [[Planet/Legends|planets]]. A large number of them were still present on [[Wayland/Legends|Wayland]] up until [[127 ABY]], when the planet was once again transformed by the [[Ossus Project]].

==Behind the scenes==
The Chom-Vrone first appeared in [[Greg Keyes]]' multi-part story ''[[Emissary of the Void]]''. [[Legacy (2006) 43|''Legacy'' (2006) 43]] misspells the name of the creature as "Chrom-Vrone."

